3E%3Cli%3E2%20tablespoons%20olive%20oil%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E1%20onion%2C%20chopped%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E1%20red%2C%20yellow%2C%20or%20orange%20pepper%2C%20chopped%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E4%20garlic%20cloves%2C%20crushed%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E1%20teaspoon%20ground%20cumin%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E2%20teaspoon%20smoked%20paprika%2C%20or%20to%20taste%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E400-gram%20tin%20of%20chopped%20tomatoes%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E400-gram%20tin%20of%20butterbeans%2C%20drained%20and%20rinsed%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESalt%20and%20freshly%20ground%20black%20pepper%2C%20to%20taste%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E2%20to%204%20eggs%2C%20depending%20on%20appetite%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20serve%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EFreshly%20chopped%20coriander%2C%20to%20taste%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EYogurt%20or%20crumbled%20feta%20cheese%20(optional)%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EDried%20chile%20flakes%2C%20to%20taste%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EZest%20of%201%20lemon%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EFlatbread%2C%20or%20warm%20crusty%20bread%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMethod%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E1.%20Heat%20the%20olive%20oil%20in%20a%20deep-set%20frying%20pan%20over%20medium%20heat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E2.%20Add%20the%20onion%20and%20pepper%20to%20the%20pan%20and%20cook%20for%20about%2010%20to%2012%20minutes%2C%20stirring%20often%2C%20until%20the%20vegetables%20start%20to%20soften.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E3.%20Add%20the%20garlic%2C%20ground%20cumin%2C%20and%20paprika%20and%20cook%20for%20about%20one%20minute%2C%20stirring%20often%2C%20until%20fragrant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E4.%20Pour%20in%20the%20chopped%20tomatoes%20and%20drained%20butterbeans%2C%20stir%20well%2C%20and%20bring%20to%20a%20simmer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E5.%20Simmer%20for%20about%2010%20to%2015%20minutes%2C%20stirring%20occasionally%2C%20until%20the%20sauce%20thickens%20slightly.%20Season%20to%20taste%2C%20adding%20more%20paprika%20if%20desired.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E6.%20Using%20the%20back%20of%20a%20large%20spoon%2C%20make%20two%20to%20four%20wells%20in%20the%20sauce%20(depending%20on%20how%20many%20eggs%20you%20intend%20to%20cook)%2C%20then%20crack%20an%20egg%20into%20each%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E7.%20Continue%20to%20cook%20for%20about%20five%20to%20seven%20minutes%2C%20or%20until%20the%20egg%20whites%20are%20set%20but%20the%20yolks%20are%20still%20runny%20(cover%20with%20a%20lid%2C%20if%20you%20have%20one%2C%20to%20speed%20up%20the%20process%20%E2%80%94%20just%20watch%20closely%20to%20ensure%20the%20eggs%20don't%20overcook).%20Once%20the%20eggs%20are%20cooked%20to%20your%20liking%2C%20remove%20the%20pan%20from%20the%20heat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E8.%20Garnish%20the%20shakshuka%20with%20coriander%2C%20yogurt%20or%20feta%20cheese%2C%20chile%20flakes%20(optional)%2C%20and%20lemon%20zest.%20Season%20with%20salt%20and%20pepper.%20Serve%20straight%20away%20with%20warm%20crusty%20bread%20or%20flatbread%20(you%20can%20present%20the%20shakshuka%20family-style%2C%20or%20dish%20it%20up%20onto%20individual%20lipped%20plates).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStorage%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%26quot%3BOnce%20you%20have%20cooked%20the%20eggs%20in%20the%20sauce%2C%20this%20dish%20is%20best%20served%20immediately.%20If%20you%20want%20to%20prepare%20your%20shakshuka%20in%20advance%2C%20you%20can%20make%20the%20sauce%20base%20by%20following%20steps%20one%20to%20five%20of%20the%20method%20shown%2C%20then%20transferring%20it%20to%20a%20Tupperware%20to%20cool%20before%20covering%20and%20chilling%20in%20the%20fridge%20for%20up%20to%20three%20days%2C%26quot%3B%20Ludlam-Raine%20said.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20are%20ready%20to%20serve%20the%20dish%2C%20simply%20return%20the%20sauce%20base%20to%20a%20pan%2C%20bring%20it%20to%20a%20simmer%2C%20then%20proceed%20with%20steps%20six%20to%20eight%20of%20the%20recipe.%20Alternatively%2C%20you%20can%20just%20reheat%20the%20base%2C%20then%20top%20with%20poached%20eggs%20that%20have%20been%20cooked%20separately.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d0494665-acf6-40b8-b8af-9aaa6c9dab17%5C%22%3EDark%20chocolate%20and%20coconut%20energy%20balls%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225504%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Dark%20chocolate%20energy%20balls%20and%20energy%20bars.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a0db49fb2b6bedb059ece6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%224128%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDark%20chocolate%20energy%20balls%2C%20pictured%20alongside%20Ludlam-Raine's%20energy%20bars%2C%20are%20a%20non-UPF%20snack.%3Cp%3EJoe%20Woodhouse%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMakes%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2010%20to%2012%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPrep%20time%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2010%20minutes%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EChill%20time%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2030%20minutes%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20are%20one%20of%20my%20go-to%20snacks%20when%20I%20am%20craving%20something%20sweet%20but%20want%20something%20more%20nutritious%20than%20a%20biscuit%20(which%2C%20of%20course%2C%20has%20its%20place%20%E2%80%94%20everything%20in%20moderation!)%2C%26quot%3B%20Ludlam-Raine%20said.%20%26quot%3BMake%20this%20recipe%20your%20own%20by%20swapping%20the%20almonds%20for%20hazelnuts%20or%20by%20experimenting%20with%20various%20nut%20butters.%20For%20extra%20flavor%2C%20toast%20the%20desiccated%20coconut%20and%20leave%20to%20cool%20completely%20before%20decorating.%20If%20you%20are%20not%20a%20fan%20of%20desiccated%20coconut%2C%20you%20can%20leave%20the%20energy%20balls%20undecorated%2C%20or%20you%20could%20roll%20them%20in%20chopped%20almonds%20instead.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBenefits%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20balls%20contain%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhealthy-fats-in-food-2018-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehealthy%20fats%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20vitamin%20E%2C%20Ludlam-Raine%20said.%20The%20combination%20of%20nuts%2C%20oats%2C%20and%20dates%20provides%20slow-release%20energy%2C%20and%20the%20fiber%20helps%20keep%20you%20satisfied.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIngredients%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20energy%20balls%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E100%20grams%20almonds%20(or%20ground%20almonds)%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E50%20grams%20good-quality%20dark%20chocolate%2C%20at%20least%2070%25%20cocoa%20solids%20(or%20chocolate%20chips)%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E10%20grams%20jumbo%20oats%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E75%20grams%20pitted%20dates%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E40%20grams%20almond%20butter%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E1%20to%202%20tablespoons%20maple%20syrup%2C%20to%20taste%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20decorate%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EAbout%2025%20grams%20desiccated%20coconut%20(optional%2C%20but%20recommended)%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMethod%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E1.%20Line%20a%20baking%20tray%20with%20non-stick%20baking%20paper%20and%20set%20aside.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E2.%20Tip%20the%20almonds%20into%20a%20food%20processor%20and%20blend%20until%20you%20have%20a%20crumb-like%20consistency%20(skip%20this%20step%20if%20you%20are%20using%20ground%20almonds).%20Add%20the%20dark%20chocolate%20and%20oats%20and%20blend%20again%20until%20you%20have%20the%20consistency%20of%20breadcrumbs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E3.%20Add%20the%20dates%2C%20almond%20butter%2C%20and%20one%20tablespoon%20of%20maple%20syrup.%20Pulse%20to%20combine.%20Taste%20to%20check%20the%20sweetness%20and%20add%20a%20little%20more%20maple%20syrup%2C%20if%20desired%2C%20before%20pulsing%20again%20to%20combine.%20Tip%20into%20a%20bowl.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E4.%20Sprinkle%20the%20baking%20tray%20with%20desiccated%20coconut%20in%20an%20even%20layer%2C%20if%20using.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E5.%20Shape%20the%20mix%20into%2010%20to%2012%20balls%20weighing%20about%2025%20to%2030%20grams%20each.%20Roll%20each%20ball%20individually%20in%20the%20desiccated%20coconut%20(optional).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E6.%20Set%20balls%20onto%20the%20baking%20tray.%20Cover%20and%20chill%20in%20the%20fridge%20for%2030%20minutes%20to%20firm%20up.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStorage%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20These%20will%20keep%20in%20an%20airtight%20container%20in%20the%20fridge%20for%20up%20to%20five%20days%2C%20and%20can%20be%20frozen%20for%20up%20to%20three%20months%2C%20Ludlam-Raine%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223cfdbf09-d05b-43c2-b3e3-56f3bf728ea6%5C%22%3EVegetable%20noodle%20stir%20fry%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225493%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20vegetable%20stir%20fry%20in%20a%20pan.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a0db88fb2b6bedb059ecf3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%228256%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EYou%20can%20add%20whatever%20protein%20source%20you%20like%20to%20a%20vegetable%20stir-fry.%3Cp%3EJoe%20Woodhouse%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EServes%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Two%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPrep%20time%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Five%20minutes%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECook%20time%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%2015%20to%2020%20minutes%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BStir%20fries%20are%20a%20brilliant%20way%20to%20make%20a%20nutritious%20meal%20in%20a%20matter%20of%20minutes.%20They%20are%20incredibly%20versatile%20and%20can%20be%20easily%20adjusted%20to%20suit%20the%20ingredients%20you%20already%20have%20at%20home%2C%20or%20adapted%20to%20accommodate%20numerous%20dietary%20requirements%2C%26quot%3B%20Ludlam-Raine%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20have%20included%20a%20suggestion%20for%20leftover%20roast%20chicken%20in%20this%20recipe%2C%20but%20you%20could%20omit%20the%20meat%20to%20keep%20this%20vegan-friendly%2C%20and%20instead%20opt%20for%20a%20plant-based%20protein%20like%20tofu.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BEqually%2C%20you%20can%20switch%20up%20the%20veggies%20for%20baby%20corn%2C%20mushrooms%2C%20mange-tout%2C%20or%20beansprouts%2C%20as%20well%20as%20try%20different%20noodles%20(egg%2C%20rice%2C%20udon%2C%20etc).%20I%20have%20included%20various%20suggestions%20for%20toppings%20to%20help%20make%20it%20family-friendly%20(not%20everyone%20likes%20chile)%20and%20to%20encourage%20diversity.%20Get%20imaginative%20and%20create%20your%20very%20own%20signature%20stir%20fry!%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBenefits%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWholewheat%20noodles%20are%20a%20good%20source%20of%20fiber%2C%20while%20peppers%20are%20high%20in%20vitamin%20C%20which%20supports%20the%20immune%20system.%20Sesame%20seeds%20add%20extra%20fiber%2C%20protein%2C%20and%20healthy%20fats%2C%20Ludlam-Raine%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIngredients%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20homemade%20stir%20fry%20sauce%20(this%20will%20make%20extra)%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E5%20tablespoons%20low-salt%20soy%20sauce%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E1%20tablespoon%20toasted%20sesame%20oil%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E1%20unwaxed%20lemon%2C%20zest%20and%20juice%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E2%20tablespoons%20runny%20honey%2C%20or%20maple%20syrup%20for%20a%20vegan%20option%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E1%20teaspoon%20garlic%20paste%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E2%20teaspoons%20ginger%20paste%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E%C2%BD%20teaspoon%20Chinese%20five%20spice%20or%20a%20pinch%20of%20dried%20chile%20flakes%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20noodles%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E2%20nests%20of%20dried%20wholewheat%20noodles%20(weighing%20about%20130%20grams)%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E100%20grams%20edamame%20beans%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E2%20spring%20onions%2Fscallions%2C%20thinly%20sliced%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E1%20carrot%2C%20grated%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E1%20tablespoon%20sesame%20oil%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20stir%20fry%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3E1%20to%202%20tablespoons%20vegetable%20oil%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E1%20red%2C%20yellow%2C%20or%20orange%20pepper%2C%20halved%2C%20deseeded%2C%20and%20thinly%20sliced%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E80%20grams%20sugar%20snap%20peas%2C%20halved%20lengthways%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAbout%203%20tablespoons%20homemade%20stir-fry%20sauce%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EAbout%20140%20grams%20cooked%20chicken%20or%20tofu%20(optional)%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E1%20to%202%20tablespoons%20water%2C%20if%20needed%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20serve%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3ESesame%20seeds%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EPeanuts%20or%20cashew%20nuts%20(optional)%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3E1%20red%20chile%2C%20thinly%20sliced%20(optional)%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ESpring%20onions%2Fscallions%2C%20thinly%20sliced%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EFreshly%20chopped%20coriander%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EMethod%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20homemade%20stir%20fry%20sauce%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E1.%20Whisk%20together%20all%20ingredients%20for%20the%20sauce%20in%20a%20small%20bowl%2C%20then%20set%20aside.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20noodles%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E1.%20Cook%20the%20noodles%20with%20the%20edamame%20beans%20according%20to%20the%20packet%20instructions%2C%20drain%20well%2C%20rinse%20under%20cold%20water%2C%20drain%20again%2C%20and%20tip%20into%20a%20bowl%20with%20the%20sliced%20spring%20onion%20and%20grated%20carrot.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E2.%20Drizzle%20with%20the%20sesame%20oil%2C%20toss%20well%2C%20and%20set%20aside.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20stir%20fry%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E1.%20Set%20a%20medium-sized%20frying%20pan%20with%20the%20vegetable%20oil%20over%20a%20medium%20heat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E2.%20When%20hot%2C%20add%20the%20peppers%20and%20sugar%20snap%20peas%20to%20the%20pan%2C%20and%20cook%20for%20five%20to%20seven%20minutes%20or%20until%20the%20veggies%20start%20to%20soften.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E3.%20Add%20the%20stir-fry%20sauce%20and%20stir%20to%20coat%20the%20vegetables.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E4.%20Remove%20from%20the%20heat%20and%20tip%20in%20the%20noodles%20and%20chicken%20or%20tofu%20(if%20using).%20Toss%20gently%20with%20the%20vegetables%20to%20coat%2C%20adding%20a%20splash%20of%20water%2C%20if%20needed%2C%20to%20loosen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E5.%20Return%20the%20pan%20to%20the%20heat%20and%20gently%20toss%20the%20contents%20for%20one%20to%20two%20minutes%20to%20heat%20through%20the%20noodles%20and%20chicken.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E6.%20Divide%20between%20two%20bowls%2C%20sprinkle%20with%20sesame%20seeds%2C%20your%20choice%20of%20nuts%2C%20sliced%20chile%20(if%20desired)%2C%20spring%20onions%2Fscallions%2C%20and%20freshly%20chopped%20coriander%2C%20and%20serve%20immediately.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStorage%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%26quot%3BThis%20dish%20is%20best%20served%20straight%20away%2C%26quot%3B%20Ludlam-Raine%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20sauce%20can%20be%20made%20in%20advance%20and%20kept%20in%20a%20sealed%20airtight%20jar%20or%20small%20container%20in%20the%20fridge%20for%20up%20to%20five%20days.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feasy-recipes-cut-down-ultra-processed-food-dietitian-2024-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1721822171000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F66a0dc7280d4d5da13d694c6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feasy-recipes-cut-down-ultra-processed-food-dietitian-2024-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20dietitian%20who%20has%20written%20a%20book%20on%20making%20eating%20fewer%20ultra-processed%20foods%20simple%20follows%20the%2080%2F20%20diet%20rule.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22rhosie%40businessinsider.com%20(Rachel%20Hosie)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Feasy-recipes-cut-down-ultra-processed-food-dietitian-2024-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22IGL%20Q1%20results%3A%20Net%20profit%20falls%208.6%25%20to%20Rs%20400%20crore%2C%20revenue%20rises%203.4%25%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1721821926000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2023-10%2F20%2Fthumb%2Ffeaturecrop%2F400X400%2F1697788160-2678.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fresults%2Figl-q1-results-net-profit-falls-8-6-to-rs-400-crore-revenue-rises-3-4-124072400912_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Total%20gas%20sale%20volumes%20rose%205.3%25%20to%20786%20million%20standard%20cubic%20meters%22%2C%22author%22%