0US%20and%20European%20countries%20would%20struggle%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20artillery%20demand%20in%20two%20different%20wars%2C%20experts%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%20one%20foresaw%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20lasting%20as%20long%20as%20it%20has%2C%20and%20I%20don't%20foresee%20Israel%20backing%20down%20any%20sooner%2C%20which%20means%20the%20simple%20cost%20of%20duration%20will%20inevitably%20impose%20a%20long-term%20strain%20on%20production%2C%26quot%3B%20Levantovscaia%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMark%20Temnycky%2C%20a%20nonresident%20fellow%20with%20the%20Atlantic%20Council's%20Eurasia%20Center%2C%20said%20the%20West's%20production%20capacities%20were%20already%20under%20pressure%20when%20Hamas%20launched%20its%20attack%20on%20Israel%20on%20October%207.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20a%20new%20war%20began%20on%20Israel's%20northern%20border%2C%20the%20West's%20industrial%20base%20would%20be%20%26quot%3Bbrought%20to%20the%20test%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20with%20pressure%20to%20supply%20defense%20equipment%20to%20Israel%20and%20Ukraine%20at%20a%20faster%20rate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20RAND's%20Cohen%2C%20%26quot%3Bany%20new%20demand%20would%20compound%20the%20supply%20issues%20with%20artillery%20rounds%20here.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20he%20noted%20that%20Israel%20would%20fight%20a%20%26quot%3Bvery%26quot%3B%20different%20type%20of%20war%20with%20Hezbollah%20than%20Ukraine%20is%20fighting%20with%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIsrael%20would%20rely%20more%20on%20air%20power%2C%20and%20Hezbollah%2C%20in%20turn%2C%20would%20rely%20on%20its%20fairly%20significant%20stockpile%20of%20rockets%20and%20drones%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAnd%20so%2C%20I%20don't%20think%20you%20would%20see%20the%20same%20number%20of%20artillery%20duels%20that%20we%20see%20currently%20in%20Ukraine.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMark%20Cancian%2C%20a%20retired%20Marine%20Corps%20colonel%20and%20senior%20advisor%20at%20the%20Center%20for%20Strategic%20and%20International%20Studies%2C%20has%20a%20different%20take.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESending%20thousands%20of%20rounds%20to%20Israel%20would%20reduce%20what%20is%20available%20for%20Ukraine%2C%20but%20%26quot%3Bthat%20would%20be%20mitigated%20by%20the%20ongoing%20increase%20in%20production%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFurther%2C%20an%20Israeli%20conflict%20with%20Hezbollah%20would%20likely%20be%20of%20short%20duration%2C%20so%20shipments%20to%20Ukraine%20would%20return%20to%20previous%20levels%20when%20the%20war%20in%20Lebanon%20ended%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22695e6dc1-f761-4832-9117-b5e7e5c06e4a%5C%22%3EUkraine%20could%20pay%20a%20price%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ECancian%20doesn't%20believe%20that%20Ukraine%20would%20run%20out%20of%20artillery%20projectiles.%20But%20it%20would%20need%20to%20prioritize%20targets%20as%20it%20did%20in%20the%20spring%2C%20when%20US%20supplies%20were%20drying%20up%2C%20he%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20would%20lead%20to%20fewer%20Ukrainian%20counterattacks%20and%20a%20more%20difficult%20time%20holding%20terrain%20on%20the%20defensive%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELevantovscaia%20said%20diverting%20artillery%20to%20Israel%20could%20potentially%20cost%20Ukraine%20the%20war%2C%20but%20said%20she%20wasn't%20%26quot%3B100%25%20sold%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20that%20Ukraine's%20innovation%20and%20determination%20could%20counterbalance%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECohen%20of%20RAND%2C%20for%20his%20part%2C%20said%20Ukraine%20has%20shown%20itself%20%26quot%3Bremarkably%20resilient%26quot%3B%20over%20the%20last%20two%20and%20a%20half%20years%20of%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMoreover%2C%20while%20the%20United%20States%20would%20want%20to%20support%20Israel%20in%20a%20war%20in%20the%20north%2C%20many%20European%20countries%20would%20likely%20still%20focus%20defense%20efforts%20on%20supporting%20Ukraine%20first%20and%20foremost%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20%26qu