%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F111986947.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EPriyanka%20Chopra%20recently%20had%20a%20gala%20time%20with%20her%20daughter%20Malti%20Marie%20and%20mother%20Madhu%20Chopra%20at%20a%20whale-watching%20trip%20in%20Australia.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fweb-stories%2Fpriyanka-chopra-aces-gen-z-fashion-in-satin-tracksuit-and-sneakers-for-whale-watching-trip%2Fphotostory%2F111986947.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%2210-Year%20Jail%2C%201-Crore%20Fine%3A%20Bihar%20Passes%20Bill%20To%20Curb%20Paper%20Leaks%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EBihar%2C%20one%20of%20the%20epicentres%20of%20several%20paper%20leaks%2C%20including%20that%20of%20the%20NEET-UG%20test%2C%20has%20passed%20a%20stringent%20bill%20to%20curb%20malpractices%20in%20government%20exams.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bihar%20Public%20Examinations%20(PE)%20(Prevention%20of%20Unfair%20Means)%20Bill%2C%202024%2C%20was%20tabled%20by%20state%20Parliamentary%20Affairs%20Minister%20Vijay%20Kumar%20Chaudhary%20on%20Wednesday%20and%20passed%20with%20a%20voice%20vote%20amid%20a%20walkout%20by%20the%20opposition.%20The%20walkout%20was%20to%20protest%20lawlessness%20and%20the%20denial%20of%20special%20status%20to%20Bihar.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bill%2C%20which%20had%20first%20been%20introduced%20in%20the%20monsoon%20session%2C%20has%20strict%20provisions%2C%20including%20a%20prison%20term%20of%20up%20to%2010%20years%20and%20a%20fine%20of%20Rs%201%20crore%20for%20those%20found%20guilty%20of%20involvement%20in%20irregularities%20in%20exams%20for%20both%20individuals%20and%20organisations.%20It%20also%20has%20a%20clause%20for%20attaching%20the%20properties%20of%20those%20found%20guilty%20and%20makes%20it%20difficult%20for%20people%20arrested%20for%20exam%20irregularities%20to%20get%20bail.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20passing%20its%20order%20on%20Tuesday%20in%20which%20it%20said%20there%20would%20be%20no%20retest%20for%20NEET-UG%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20bench%20led%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20DY%20Chandrachud%20had%20also%20noted%20that%20the%20paper%20for%20the%20exam%20had%20been%20leaked%20for%20at%20least%20two%20centres%2C%20in%20Bihar's%20Patna%20and%20Hazaribagh%20in%20Jharkhand.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBihar%20has%20seen%20several%20paper%20leaks%20for%20state-level%20tests%20and%20gangs%20from%20the%20state%20have%20also%20been%20found%20involved%20in%20leaking%20papers%20or%20tampering%20with%20the%20examination%20process%20for%20national%20entrance%20exams.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20state's%20paper%20leak%20bill%20follows%20the%20notification%20of%20a%20central%20law%20last%20month.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20Public%20Examinations%20(Prevention%20of%20Unfair%20Means)%20Act%2C%202024%2C%20which%20was%20notified%20on%20June%2021%2C%20any%20person%20or%20persons%20found%20guilty%20of%20leaking%20a%20paper%20or%20tampering%20with%20answer%20sheets%20will%20receive%20a%20minimum%20jail%20term%20of%20three%20years.%20This%20can%20be%20extended%20to%20five%20years%20with%20a%20fine%20of%20up%20to%20Rs%2010%20lakh.%20All%20offences%20under%20the%20Act%20will%20be%20cognisable%20and%20non-bailable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EExamination%20service%20providers%20who%20have%20knowledge%20about%20a%20possible%20offence%20but%20do%20not%20report%20it%20can%20be%20fined%20up%20to%20Rs%201%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%20investigation%2C%20if%20it%20is%20established%20that%20any%20senior%20official%20from%20the%20service%20provider%20had%20allowed%20or%20was%20involved%20in%20committing%20the%20offence%2C%20he%20will%20face%20imprisonment%20for%20a%20minimum%20of%20three%20years%2C%20which%20can%20go%20up%20to%2010%20years%2C%20and%20a%20fine%20of%20Rs%201%20c