%3A%2F%2Fwww.instagram.com%2Fp%2FBgRvOdmhvs-%2F%3Futm_source%3Dig_embed%26utm_campaign%3Dloading%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EA%20post%20shared%20by%20Shish%20Mahal%20(%40officialshishmahal)%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%20%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20the%20name%20and%20fame%20of%20the%20chicken%20%3Cem%3Etikka%20masala%3C%2Fem%3E%20spread%20far%20and%20wide%2C%20and%20restaurants%20in%20England%20were%20quick%20to%20clone%20the%20idea%2C%20furthering%20its%20legacy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChef%20Ali%20passed%20in%202022%20at%20the%20age%20of%2077%2C%20but%20not%20before%20he%20gave%20multiple%20interviews%20that%20were%20all%20aimed%20at%20finding%20out%20where%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F309836%2Ffood-history-of-idli-sambar-roots-in-indonesia-south-indian-breakfast%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eorigins%20of%20the%20dish%3C%2Fa%3E%20truly%20lie.%20In%20one%20of%20his%20interviews%20with%20AFP%2C%20Ali%20seconded%20the%20theory%20that%20the%20%3Cem%3Etikka%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewas%20his%20creation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CChicken%20%3Cem%3Etikka%20masala%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewas%20invented%20in%20this%20%5BShish%20Mahal%5D%20restaurant.%20We%20used%20to%20make%20%3Cem%3Echicken%20tikka%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20and%20one%20day%20a%20customer%20said%2C%20%E2%80%98I%E2%80%99d%20take%20some%20sauce%20with%20that%2C%20this%20is%20a%20bit%20dry%E2%80%99.%20We%20thought%20we%E2%80%99d%20better%20cook%20the%20chicken%20with%20some%20sauce.%20So%20from%20here%2C%20we%20cooked%20chicken%20%3Cem%3Etikka%20%3C%2Fem%3Ewith%20a%20sauce%20that%20contains%20yoghurt%2C%20cream%2C%20and%20spices.%20It%E2%80%99s%20a%20dish%20prepared%20according%20to%20our%20customer%E2%80%99s%20taste.%20Usually%2C%20they%20don%E2%80%99t%20take%20hot%20curry%20%E2%80%93%20that%E2%80%99s%20why%20we%20cook%20it%20with%20yoghurt%20and%20cream.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EWho%20is%20taking%20the%20prize%20home%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20really%20set%20the%20stage%20for%20debate%2C%20was%20a%20speech%20made%20in%202001%20by%20the%20then-British%20foreign%20secretary%20Robin%20Cook%20who%20hailed%20the%20chicken%20%3Cem%3Etikka%20masala%3C%2Fem%3E%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Ctrue%20British%20national%20dish%E2%80%9D.%20Indians%20weren%E2%80%99t%20thrilled%20with%20this%20claim.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Cook%20went%20on%2C%20%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6not%20only%20because%20it%20is%20the%20most%20popular%2C%20but%20because%20it%20is%20a%20perfect%20illustration%20of%20the%20way%20Britain%20absorbs%20and%20adapts%20external%20influences.%20Chicken%20%3Cem%3Etikka%20%3C%2Fem%3Eis%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F60553%2Fhistory-biryani-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ean%20Indian%20dish%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20%3Cem%3Emasala%20%3C%2Fem%3Esauce%20was%20added%20to%20satisfy%20the%20desire%20of%20British%20people%20to%20have%20their%20meat%20served%20in%20gravy.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20followed%20by%20another%20attempt%20in%202009%20to%20pin%20the%20dish%E2%80%99s%20origin%20to%20Europe%20when%20Mohammad%20Sarwar%2C%20then%20Labour%20MP%20for%20Glasgow%20Central%2C%20campaigned%20for%20the%20dish%20to%20be%20given%20EU%20Protected%20Designation%20of%20Origin%20status.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20motion%20was%20tabled%20by%20the%20House%20of%20Commons.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ciframe%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22strict-origin-when-cross-origin%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2FTzYACT9nT7A%3Fsi%3Dl7zeE0Cp3SioKMoC%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20were%20starting%20to%20think%20that%20the%20war%20of%20chicken%20%3Cem%3Etikka%20masala%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99s%20origins%20were%20just%20between%20the%20two%20subcontinents%20(India%20and%20Europe)%2C%20you%20are%20wrong.%20Even%20within%20India%2C%20the%20origin%20stands%20to%20be%20debated%20%E2%80%94%20is%20it%20Mogul%20or%20%3Cem%3EPunjabi%3C%2Fem%3E%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EZaeemuddin%20Ahmad%20of%20the%20iconic%20Karim%E2%80%99s%20restaurant%20in%20Delhi%2C%20is%20of%20the%20first%20opinion%2C%20saying%20the%20recipe%20was%20passed%20down%20through%20the%20generations%20in%20his%20family.%20As%20he%20relayed%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Daily%20Telegraph%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CChicken%20%3Cem%3Etikka%20masala%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20an%20authentic%20Mughlai%20recipe%20prepared%20by%20our%20forefathers%20who%20were%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F157345%2Fmughal-emperor-mughlai-food-history-india-news%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eroyal%20chefs%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20Mughal%20period.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20food%20critic%20Rahul%20Verma%20claims%20to%20have%20first%20tasted%20chicken%20%3Cem%3Etikka%20masala%3C%2Fem%3E%20in%201971%20and%20insists%20it%20is%20a%20%3Cem%3EPunjabi%20%3C%2Fem%3Edish.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20belief%20is%20shared%20by%20many%20who%20see%20the%20chicken%20%3Cem%3Etikka%20masala%20%3C%2Fem%3Eas%20a%20mutation%20of%20the%20butter%20chicken%2C%20which%20is%20(and%20this%20is%20set%20in%20stone)%20the%20creation%20of%20Kundan%20Lal%20Gujral%2C%20the%20man%20behind%20Moti%20Mahal%20restaurant%20in%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20look-alikes%2C%20the%20butter%20chicken%20and%20chicken%20%3Cem%3Etikka%20masala%3C%2Fem%3E%20differ%20in%20their%20taste%20palate%20and%20the%20hero%20ingredient%20(aside%20from%20chicken)%20that%20they%20feature%3B%20the%20former%20has%20copious%20amounts%20of%20butter%2C%20and%20a%20sweeter%20taste%2C%20while%20the%20latter%20is%20on%20the%20spicier%20side.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENaved%20Nasir%2C%20executive%20chef%20of%20the%20UK%E2%80%99s%20popular%20Dishoom%20does%20not%20favour%20this%20opinion%20o